{{for|the Wikiproject about names pages|Wikipedia:WikiProject Anthroponymy}}

'''Anthroponomastics''' (or '''anthroponymy''') is the study of the [[Personal name|names]] of [[human being]]s.<ref name="Fossier2010">{{cite book|author=Robert Fossier|title=The Axe and the Oath: Ordinary Life in the Middle Ages|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=28-W9XslC9MC&pg=PA34|date=2010|location=Princeton, NJ|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-3614-7|page=34}}</ref> The study of anthroponyms (from [[Ancient Greek]] ἄνθρωπος ''anthrōpos'', 'human' and ὄνομα ''onoma'', 'name') is a branch of [[onomastics]]. Linguists and researchers in many other fields take part in anthroponymic studies, including anthropologists,<ref name="Felecan2012">
{{cite book | author=Oliviu Felecan|title=Name and Naming: Synchronic and Diachronic Perspectives|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FT8sBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA18 | date=2012 | publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing | isbn=978-1-4438-3807-8 | page=18}}</ref> historians,<ref>
{{cite journal| last=Ziolkowska | first=Magdalena | title=Anthroponomy as an Element Identifying National Minority | url=http://jeful.ut.ee/public/files/Magdalena+Ziolkowska+383-398.pdf | journal= Eesti Ja Soome-ugri Keeleteaduse Ajakiri. Journal of Estonian and Finno-Ugric Linguistics (ESUKA – JEFUL) | year=2011 | volume=2 | number=1 | pages=383–398}}</ref> political geographers
<ref>Rodríguez, Francisco Javier Pérez. (March 4, 2012). [http://scholarworks.iu.edu/journals/index.php/tmr/article/view/17494/23612 Review] of ''Anthroponymie et migrations dans la chrétienté médiévale (Anthroponymy and Migration in Medieval Christianity)'' edited by Monique Bourin and Pascual Martínez Sopena. ''[https://scholarworks.iu.edu/journals/index.php/tmr/index The Medieval Review]''. Indiana University. Retrieved September 11, 2017.</ref> and genealogists.

Subdivisions of anthroponymy include:
*[[Given name]]s
*[[Surname]]s
*[[Clan|Clan name]]s
*[[Matronym]]s
*[[Patronym]]s
*[[Teknonymy|Teknonyms]]
*[[Nickname]]s
*[[Demonym]]s
*[[Ethnonym]]s
**[[endonym|Autonym]]s/[[Endonym]]s
**[[Exonym]]s

